					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">WedNESday wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">1. According to Loopy, writes to $2000 (bits 0 and 1) instantly change the NT being used. However, when I include this in my code it breaks most Nintendo games. When I remove it, it fixes most games, but of course some games don't change NT when they are supposed to. Can anyone add anything further?</div><br /><br />Writes to $2000 update PPU.TMPAddress, not PPU.Address (as you seem to have figured out).<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">WedNESday wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">2. Loopy's Skinny on NES scrolling also says that...<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">case 257:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;if&#40; PPU.Visibility &amp;&amp; Sprite.Visibility &#41;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&#123;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;PPU.Address &amp;= 0x7BE0;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;PPU.Address += &#40;PPU.TMPAddress &amp; 0x041F&#41;;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&#125;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;break;<br />case 304:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;if&#40; PPU.Visibility &amp;&amp; Sprite.Visibility &#41;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;PPU.Address = PPU.TMPAddress;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;break;</div><br /><br />...if PPU and Sprites are on that the code above it executed. However, when I change it to || instead of &amp;&amp;, again, the games work. Is it || or &amp;&amp;?</div><br /><br />It's ||, and the case for 304 only happens before the first rendered scanline.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">WedNESday wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">3. In terms of Colour Intensity, I have read documents that provide numbers to intensify the colours when the bits are set. I was wondering how these numbers where obtained and what numbers do you use?</div>
<br />
<br />My emulator has a simplified set of colour emphasis coefficients (download the sources and check GFX.c, it's in there somewhere), but I only use it for imported palettes (i.e. .PAL files) - for NTSC, I generate and parse the NTSC waveforms for each color and emphasis combination to generate the palette.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Quietust, QMT Productions
<br />P.S. If you don't get this note, let me know and I'll write you another.</div>
