					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">WedNESday wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">When the PPU and Sprites are off, then the PPU enters some kind of sleep state, are there no memory fetches and no dead cycle?.</div>
<br />
<br />What do you mean by "dead cycle"?
<br />
<br />The last cycle on the pre-render scanline on odd frames isn't skipped (if that's what you were referring to).
<br />
<br />And yeah -- $3F00 gets rendered -- unless the PPU address is set to $3Fxx (or any mirrored range), in which case, the color the address is pointing to is being rendered.  Many Camerica games rely on this effect (notably, Bee 52 and Micro Machines)</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

