						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">If a game has not VROM, then that area becomes VRAM. However, how does the NES know if that PPU area is VROM or VRAM? Is there some kind of flag somewhere?</div>
<br />If a cartridge doesn't have a CHR ROM, it <em>must</em> have CHR RAM, since the NES doesn't have any video memory on-board for the $0000-$1FFF region (it only has nametable memory).</div>

