				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">What Bregalad described actually does put CHR ROM on the cartridge, part of a shared ROM. A real exception would be to somehow make the PPU use the internal pattern table memory for pattern data as well. I'm not sure if that would be possible. My main point was that a cartridge was not like an iNES file, with either CHR ROM data or nothing; in place of nothing it has CHR RAM, obviously not necessary in a file, other than the CHR bank count bits being cleared.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

