				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">According to Brad Taylor;
<br />
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">Memory fetch phase 1 thru 128<br />-----------------------------<br />1. Name table byte<br />2. Attribute table byte<br />3. Pattern table bitmap #0<br />4. Pattern table bitmap #1<br /><br />This process is repeated 32 times &#40;32 tiles in a scanline&#41;.</div>
<br />
<br />Let's say that after the name table byte has been fetched, the PPU address is modified. Does the PPU remember which name table byte it fetched or would the attribute table byte be for the new name table byte? (Same goes for the Bitmaps)</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.jamesturner.de/">http://www.jamesturner.de/</a><!-- m --></div>
